<DOC><DOCNO> ZF310-604-757 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 604 757.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  April 15 1991 n416 pS2(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Comp USA to mail 20 million catalogs: named changed from SoftWarehouse.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Trespasz, Nancy; Markowitz, Elliot.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Comp USA, formerly Soft Warehouse, is preparing to launch aconsumer catalog program, signalling a shift in the chain'sadvertising expenditures.andP;  The company will mail 20 millioncatalogs in 1991.andP;  CompuAdd Corp, the self-proclaimed secondbiggest catalog house worldwide, mails about 25 million catalogsannually.andP;  Comp USA is cutting its newspaper advertising costs by30 to 40 percent to offset expenses of the catalog program.andP;  Thecatalogs will also be partially financed by vendors' marketdevelopment funds and co-op money.andP;  The company has made athree-year commitment to the catalog program.andP;  Some 18 differenttypes of catalogs will be printed, ranging in sizes from 16 to 128pages.andP;  They will include a toll-free number for orderingmerchandise over the phone.andP;  The chief goal is to draw customersinto the chain's superstores.andP;  Different catalogs will be sent todifferent types of customers, such as large corporations, smallbusinesses and home users.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   CompUSA Inc. (Marketing).andO;Topic:     Marketing StrategyComputer RetailingDirect MarketingCatalogsAdvertising.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>